## Milestone 7 — Skills & martial arts

Replace the **Skills** and **Martial Arts** placeholders with full editing.

### Rules / models

- `skill-totals.ts` — effective rating = base + `ImprovementType.Skill` / `SkillGroup` / `SkillCategory` bonuses
- Skill requirement checks (`requirement-validator.ts` extended for skill prerequisites)
- `martial-art-calculator.ts` — style rating BP (`bpMartialArt`), maneuver costs
- Default vs non-default skill handling from `skills.json` (`default: Yes/No`)

### UI

- **Skills** tab: browse/filter active skills (reuse `SourceFilterControl`), set ratings and specializations
- Skill groups sub-section (buy group vs individual skills)
- Knowledge & language skills sub-section
- **Martial Arts** tab: add style, set rating, list maneuvers from data
- Show effective rating (base + quality/cyberware bonuses) read-only where relevant

### Store

- `CharacterStoreService` methods: `setSkillRating`, `setSkillSpec`, `addMartialArt`, etc.
- Feed skill list into selection handlers (`selectskill`, `selectskillgroup`) for quality grants

### Persistence / import

- Import/export skills and martial arts sections from `.chum`

### Tests

- Aptitude + skill rating interaction
- College Education category bonus on ratings
- Martial art rating BP cap (35 BP positive-quality interaction)

### Legacy reference

- `frmCreate.cs` — skill list UI logic (extract BP rules, not TreeView code)

### Done when

Skills, knowledge skills, and one martial art contribute to BP breakdown and validation; quality skill pickers offer real character skills.

