## Milestone 8 — Street gear & availability

Replace the **Street Gear** placeholder. Reuse reference-browser patterns for gear, weapons, and armor.

### Rules / models

- Extend `PurchasedItem` (or add `CharacterGear`, `CharacterWeapon`, `CharacterArmor`) with parent/child nesting, mods, accessories
- `gear-calculator.ts` — nuyen cost, cost formulas via `evaluateFormula()`
- Wire `validateAvailability()` into `validateCharacter()` via `availabilityItems` built from purchases
- Restricted item count from `ImprovementType.RestrictedItemCount`

### UI

- **Street Gear** tab with sub-sections: Gear, Weapons (+ accessories/mods), Armor (+ mods)
- Browse/add/remove items; show avail, cost, remaining nuyen
- PACKS kit loader (optional stretch: apply `packs.json` as a bundle)
- Source filter (`SourceFilterControl`) on all browse lists

### Store

- `addPurchase` / `removePurchase` with nested children
- Auto-update `character.purchases` for nuyen breakdown

### Persistence / import

- Import `<gears>`, `<weapons>`, `<armors>` from `.chum` (warn on unsupported nested sections initially)

### Tests

- Availability violation detection
- Nuyen overspend validation
- Formula-based gear cost (rating-dependent items)

### Legacy reference

- `frmCreate.cs` — nuyen spending, availability enforcement
- `clsCharacter.cs` — gear tree structure

### Done when

A character can buy core-rulebook gear within avail and nuyen limits; BP Summary nuyen section reflects purchases.

