## Milestone 9 — Cyberware & bioware

Replace the **Cyberware** placeholder. Essence and augmentation bonuses integrate with the improvement system.

### Rules / models

- `CharacterCyberware`, `CharacterBioware` tree models (grade, rating, children, essence cost)
- `essence-calculator.ts` — ESS from base 6 minus ware; support `essencemin` from metatype
- `ware-calculator.ts` — nuyen + availability + essence cost
- Apply ware `bonus` nodes through `applyBonusHandlers()` (many handlers already exist; add missing ones as encountered)
- Validation: essence floor (0.01), over-max availability, magic loss thresholds

### UI

- **Cyberware** tab: category tree browser, add/remove ware, grade/rating pickers
- Bioware section (same tab or sub-nav)
- Show current essence, lost essence, remaining capacity
- Disable incompatible ware where data `required`/`forbidden` blocks it

### Store

- Transaction-safe ware install/remove (rollback improvements on failure)

### Persistence / import

- Import `<cyberwares>`, `<biowares>` from `.chum`

### Tests

- Essence math with graded cyberware
- Ware bonus applied (e.g. attribute bonuses, skill bonuses)
- Magic/resonance reduction thresholds (if applicable from ware)

### Legacy reference

- `frmCreate.cs` — cyberware install, essence penalties
- `clsImprovement.cs` — ware bonus handlers

### Done when

Cyberware/bioware installs adjust ESS and improvements correctly; removing ware rolls back bonuses.

