## Milestone 10 — Magic, matrix, vehicles & career

Replace remaining conditional tabs and close the creation loop with export and career transition.

### Rules / models

- `CharacterSpell`, `CharacterPower`, `CharacterProgram`, `CharacterMetamagic`, `CharacterInitiationGrade`, `CharacterVehicle`
- BP/karma cost calculators per type (spells, adept powers, programs, initiation grades)
- Tradition/stream selection updates `magicTradition` / `technomancerStream` and enables validation rules already in `character-validator.ts`

### UI

- **Magician** tab: tradition picker, spells (free spells, BP purchases), bound spirits (stretch)
- **Adept** tab: power picker with point allocation
- **Technomancer** tab: stream picker, programs/complex forms (basic list + rating)
- **Critter** tab: critter powers from metatype/quality (mostly read-only + BP display)
- **Initiation** tab: grades, metamagic/echoes when enabled
- **Vehicles** tab: vehicle/drone list with mods (basic add/remove)
- **BP Summary** tab: extend with skills, gear, ware, magic line items

### Persistence / export

- `chum-exporter.ts` — serialize full character to `.chum` XML (mirror importer field order)
- Expand `chum-importer.ts` for spells, powers, programs, vehicles, lifestyles, martial arts
- `created` flag + career mode entry (read-only creation BP or karma advancement stub)

### Validation & finalize

- “Finalize character” action: set `created: true`, run full validation suite
- Block finalize when overspent BP/nuyen, avail violations, or missing tradition/stream

### Tests

- Magician with tradition + spells validates
- Adept power point cap
- Round-trip: export → import preserves character state (golden `.chum` fixture)

### Legacy reference

- `frmCreate.cs` — spell/power BP, initiation
- `clsCharacter.cs` — Save() XML structure

### Done when

A magician adept (or other enabled build) can be created end-to-end, exported as `.chum`, re-imported, and marked created for career mode.

